<subSubSection pageId="24" pageNumber="133" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="24.[189,335,547,573]" box="[189,335,547,573]" pageId="24" pageNumber="133">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,335,547,573]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="24" pageNumber="133" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,335,547,573]" pageId="24" pageNumber="133">Description</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[189,917,594,656]" box="[234,378,594,621]" pageId="24" pageNumber="133">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[234,298,594,620]" pageId="24" pageNumber="133">Male</emphasis>
(n=2)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[189,917,594,656]" box="[189,917,629,656]" pageId="24" pageNumber="133">
Length: 
<quantity box="[288,388,629,656]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="24" pageNumber="133" unit="mm" value="5.5" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="5.0">5–6 mm</quantity>
. Differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="Santos &amp; Pape &amp; Mello-Patiu, 2022" authorityName="Santos &amp; Pape &amp; Mello-Patiu" authorityYear="2022" box="[553,684,629,655]" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Dexosarcophaga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="133" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phoenix" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[553,684,629,655]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="133">D. phoenix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[691,782,630,656]" pageId="24" pageNumber="133" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
as follows:
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[185,1399,695,1038]" pageId="24" pageNumber="133">
Frons about0.30 × head width at level of ocellar triangle; 7–9 well-developed frontal setae reaching level of apex of pedicel; gena and genal groove with slightly yellowish-silver pollinosity (
<figureCitation box="[1129,1237,730,756]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="24.[189,232,1964,1990]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,1517,1926]" captionTargetId="figure-292@24.[189,1398,1517,1926]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="Fig. 13. Dexosarcophaga pallida sp. nov., ♂, paratype (NHRS [lost]), Colombia, Caquetá, Chiribiquete National Park. A. Habitus, lateral view. B. Terminalia, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6823758" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6823758/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="133">Fig. 13A</figureCitation>
); acrostichals 3 (weakly differentiated) + 1; dorsocentrals 4 (anteriormost shorter) +3 (two minor anterior); intra-alars 2+ 2; meral setae 5–7; abdomen dark brown, with slightly yellowish-silver pollinosity; T4 with 1–2 pairs of lateral marginal setae; row of about 10 marginal setae on T5; marginal setae of ST2–4 slightly differentiated from discal setae; short median incision at posterior margin of ST5 (
<figureCitation box="[1163,1273,871,897]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="23.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[238,1319,280,1815]" captionTargetId="figure-11@23.[232,1356,265,1855]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="Fig. 12. Dexosarcophaga pallida sp. nov., ♂, holotype (NHRS [lost]). A. Sternite 5, ventral view. B. Syntergosternite 7+8, epandrium, cercus and surstylus, lateral view. C. Cerci, posterior view. D. Phallus and associated structures, lateral view. E. Distiphallus, ventral view. Abbreviations: see Material and methods. Scale bars =0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6823756" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6823756/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="133">Fig. 12A</figureCitation>
); surstylus slightly curved (
<figureCitation box="[380,487,906,932]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="23.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[238,1319,280,1815]" captionTargetId="figure-11@23.[232,1356,265,1855]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="Fig. 12. Dexosarcophaga pallida sp. nov., ♂, holotype (NHRS [lost]). A. Sternite 5, ventral view. B. Syntergosternite 7+8, epandrium, cercus and surstylus, lateral view. C. Cerci, posterior view. D. Phallus and associated structures, lateral view. E. Distiphallus, ventral view. Abbreviations: see Material and methods. Scale bars =0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6823756" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6823756/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="133">Fig. 12B</figureCitation>
); vesica narrow at base and expanded at apex in ventral view (
<figureCitation box="[1214,1320,906,932]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="23.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[238,1319,280,1815]" captionTargetId="figure-11@23.[232,1356,265,1855]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="Fig. 12. Dexosarcophaga pallida sp. nov., ♂, holotype (NHRS [lost]). A. Sternite 5, ventral view. B. Syntergosternite 7+8, epandrium, cercus and surstylus, lateral view. C. Cerci, posterior view. D. Phallus and associated structures, lateral view. E. Distiphallus, ventral view. Abbreviations: see Material and methods. Scale bars =0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6823756" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6823756/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="133">Fig. 12E</figureCitation>
); juxta arching over acrophallus, strongly membranous, smooth and not clearly differentiated from paraphallus (
<figureCitation box="[197,341,976,1002]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="23.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[238,1319,280,1815]" captionTargetId="figure-11@23.[232,1356,265,1855]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="Fig. 12. Dexosarcophaga pallida sp. nov., ♂, holotype (NHRS [lost]). A. Sternite 5, ventral view. B. Syntergosternite 7+8, epandrium, cercus and surstylus, lateral view. C. Cerci, posterior view. D. Phallus and associated structures, lateral view. E. Distiphallus, ventral view. Abbreviations: see Material and methods. Scale bars =0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6823756" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6823756/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="133">Fig. 12D–E</figureCitation>
); median stylus narrow and with apical spines (
<figureCitation box="[906,1050,976,1002]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="23.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[238,1319,280,1815]" captionTargetId="figure-11@23.[232,1356,265,1855]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="Fig. 12. Dexosarcophaga pallida sp. nov., ♂, holotype (NHRS [lost]). A. Sternite 5, ventral view. B. Syntergosternite 7+8, epandrium, cercus and surstylus, lateral view. C. Cerci, posterior view. D. Phallus and associated structures, lateral view. E. Distiphallus, ventral view. Abbreviations: see Material and methods. Scale bars =0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6823756" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6823756/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="133">Fig. 12D–E</figureCitation>
); lateral stylus equipped with strong spines apically and base curved towards ventral margin of paraphallus (
<figureCitation box="[1110,1253,1011,1038]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="23.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[238,1319,280,1815]" captionTargetId="figure-11@23.[232,1356,265,1855]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="Fig. 12. Dexosarcophaga pallida sp. nov., ♂, holotype (NHRS [lost]). A. Sternite 5, ventral view. B. Syntergosternite 7+8, epandrium, cercus and surstylus, lateral view. C. Cerci, posterior view. D. Phallus and associated structures, lateral view. E. Distiphallus, ventral view. Abbreviations: see Material and methods. Scale bars =0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6823756" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6823756/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="133">Fig. 12D–E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
