<subSubSection lastPageId="25" lastPageNumber="134" pageId="24" pageNumber="133" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="24.[189,304,1290,1316]" box="[189,304,1290,1316]" pageId="24" pageNumber="133">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,304,1290,1316]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="24" pageNumber="133" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,304,1290,1316]" pageId="24" pageNumber="133">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[189,1399,1336,1468]" lastBlockId="25.[188,1398,265,433]" lastPageId="25" lastPageNumber="134" pageId="24" pageNumber="133">
<taxonomicName authority="Santos &amp; Pape &amp; Mello-Patiu, 2022" authorityName="Santos &amp; Pape &amp; Mello-Patiu" authorityYear="2022" box="[189,482,1336,1362]" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Dexosarcophaga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="133" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pallida" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[189,482,1336,1362]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="133">Dexosarcophaga pallida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[490,580,1337,1363]" pageId="24" pageNumber="133" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is morphologically similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Dodge, 1968" authorityName="Dodge" authorityYear="1968" box="[934,1395,1336,1362]" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Dexosarcophaga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="133" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="currani">
<emphasis box="[934,1232,1336,1362]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="133">Dexosarcophaga currani</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Dodge H. R." box="[1240,1395,1336,1362]" pageId="24" pageNumber="133" pagination="421 - 450" refId="ref10829" refString="Dodge H. R. 1968. The Sarcophagidae of Barro Colorado Island, Panama (Diptera). Annals of the Entomological Society of America 61: 421 - 450. https: // doi. org / 10.1093 / aesa / 61.2.421" type="journal article" year="1968">Dodge, 1968</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. Males of both species have a stick-like vesica in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[920,1029,1371,1397]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="23.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[238,1319,280,1815]" captionTargetId="figure-11@23.[232,1356,265,1855]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="Fig. 12. Dexosarcophaga pallida sp. nov., ♂, holotype (NHRS [lost]). A. Sternite 5, ventral view. B. Syntergosternite 7+8, epandrium, cercus and surstylus, lateral view. C. Cerci, posterior view. D. Phallus and associated structures, lateral view. E. Distiphallus, ventral view. Abbreviations: see Material and methods. Scale bars =0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6823756" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6823756/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="133">Fig. 12D</figureCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Mello-Patiu C. A." box="[1042,1253,1371,1397]" pageId="24" pageNumber="133" pagination="1 - 16" refId="ref11376" refString="Mello-Patiu C. A. 2002. Revision of some Dexosarcophaga species described by R. Dodge (Diptera: Sarcophagidae). Zootaxa 122: 1 - 16." type="journal article" year="2002">Mello-Patiu 2002</bibRefCitation>
: figs 53, 56) and a membranous projection from the ventral part of the paraphallus at the level of the acrophallus (
<figureCitation box="[198,305,1442,1468]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="23.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[238,1319,280,1815]" captionTargetId="figure-11@23.[232,1356,265,1855]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="Fig. 12. Dexosarcophaga pallida sp. nov., ♂, holotype (NHRS [lost]). A. Sternite 5, ventral view. B. Syntergosternite 7+8, epandrium, cercus and surstylus, lateral view. C. Cerci, posterior view. D. Phallus and associated structures, lateral view. E. Distiphallus, ventral view. Abbreviations: see Material and methods. Scale bars =0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6823756" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6823756/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="133">Fig. 12D</figureCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Mello-Patiu C. A." box="[316,525,1442,1468]" pageId="24" pageNumber="133" pagination="1 - 16" refId="ref11376" refString="Mello-Patiu C. A. 2002. Revision of some Dexosarcophaga species described by R. Dodge (Diptera: Sarcophagidae). Zootaxa 122: 1 - 16." type="journal article" year="2002">Mello-Patiu 2002</bibRefCitation>
: figs 53, 56). The latter projection may be formed by the paraphallus or be a composite of both the paraphallus and the juxta. These two species can be differentiated by the following features: vesica strongly bifurcated at apex (
<figureCitation box="[724,832,300,326]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="23.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[238,1319,280,1815]" captionTargetId="figure-11@23.[232,1356,265,1855]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="Fig. 12. Dexosarcophaga pallida sp. nov., ♂, holotype (NHRS [lost]). A. Sternite 5, ventral view. B. Syntergosternite 7+8, epandrium, cercus and surstylus, lateral view. C. Cerci, posterior view. D. Phallus and associated structures, lateral view. E. Distiphallus, ventral view. Abbreviations: see Material and methods. Scale bars =0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6823756" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6823756/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="134">Fig. 12E</figureCitation>
) and lateral and median styli approximately ⅓ the length of paraphallus (
<figureCitation box="[515,659,335,361]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="23.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[238,1319,280,1815]" captionTargetId="figure-11@23.[232,1356,265,1855]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="Fig. 12. Dexosarcophaga pallida sp. nov., ♂, holotype (NHRS [lost]). A. Sternite 5, ventral view. B. Syntergosternite 7+8, epandrium, cercus and surstylus, lateral view. C. Cerci, posterior view. D. Phallus and associated structures, lateral view. E. Distiphallus, ventral view. Abbreviations: see Material and methods. Scale bars =0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6823756" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6823756/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="134">Fig. 12D–E</figureCitation>
) in 
<taxonomicName authority="Santos &amp; Pape &amp; Mello-Patiu, 2022" authorityName="Santos &amp; Pape &amp; Mello-Patiu" authorityYear="2022" box="[714,1012,335,361]" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Dexosarcophaga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="134" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pallida" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[714,1012,335,361]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="134">Dexosarcophaga pallida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1024,1122,336,362]" pageId="25" pageNumber="134" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, versus vesica slightly bifurcated at apex (
<bibRefCitation author="Mello-Patiu C. A." box="[417,631,370,397]" pageId="25" pageNumber="134" pagination="1 - 16" refId="ref11376" refString="Mello-Patiu C. A. 2002. Revision of some Dexosarcophaga species described by R. Dodge (Diptera: Sarcophagidae). Zootaxa 122: 1 - 16." type="journal article" year="2002">Mello-Patiu 2002</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 58) and lateral and median styli approximately ½ the length of paraphallus (
<bibRefCitation author="Mello-Patiu C. A." box="[372,585,406,432]" pageId="25" pageNumber="134" pagination="1 - 16" refId="ref11376" refString="Mello-Patiu C. A. 2002. Revision of some Dexosarcophaga species described by R. Dodge (Diptera: Sarcophagidae). Zootaxa 122: 1 - 16." type="journal article" year="2002">Mello-Patiu 2002</bibRefCitation>
: figs 53, 56–57) in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dodge" authorityYear="1968" box="[809,1107,406,432]" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Dexosarcophaga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="134" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="currani">
<emphasis box="[809,1107,406,432]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="134">Dexosarcophaga currani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
